      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. It's just that the board has been very sensitive to volatility in recent quarters, and they've been looking for any reason to tighten the budget on XJ-9. If I present a 99% confidence level alongside that much visible variance, they might think we're overstating the stability to secure the next round of funding. To be absolutely certain, if we were to strip back the Bayesian priors and look at a purely frequentist analysis of the Phase II data alone, would that confidence level hold up, or is there a risk it would drop significantly?",
